	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103668418878701><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>amend</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=97537><span id= >Rive the Wise</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>11 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Nov 7th 10:49 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>what I meant to say is that none of the really good shammy armor is deity specific.... so don't worry about it. =P<br><br>OK so While im here jabberin I might as well offer some strategy as to the quickest way to lvl IMO. I Shaman of the 39th season. I have seen and done much in my days and have enjoyed playing my shaman the whole way.<br><br>lvl 1-10 - You should get these lvls in your newbie zone (in this case I am referring to Vah Shir shamans) In the pit and out in Shadeweavers Thicket. <br>lvl 12-26 - Paludal Caverns ALL THE WAY. This place rocks. You start out right inside the actualy caverns fighting Muckdiggers and such like that. Then you slowly move deeper and start fighting mushrooms and the more powerful muckdiggers. Then at about lvl 15 start fighting Phatog flarg fiends. Or just get invis and run over to the Bandit camps. But fight the bandits from lvl 15 all the way till 26 or so. The EXP is best in the game and the loot and pp is decent if your quick to loot. <br><br>lvl 26-35 - Highhold Keep - Get in a good group here and fight Goblins all the way till lvl 36 or so. The exp is decent and the loot sells good with the right amount of charisma. As soon as you hit about lvl 33 or so get in a group in the WR or RR (warrior room or Raider Room) If you want a change of pace and or you ant to speed up the pulls (which tend to be slow sometimes) then start pulling and killing guards. You only take a faction hit with the guards in Highkeep and the evil guards in freeport. The guards give really good EXP and they are just plain fun to kill.<br><br>lvl 35-45 - Velious and Kunark - In velious hook up a group in the Crystal Caverns. You get some good loot like the herbalist pack and the CCS and the exp is bonus cause its a dungeon. Also if you can go to the Nexus and hook up with C3 you can take the Nexus Scion down to Velious and using your pet and instill you can solo Dire wolves. I did this alot and got about 4% exp PER KILL. that rocks. you have to really watch your back and know the way to thurgadin by heart because it is very easy to get a frost giant on your a$$. Frost giant = BAD.... =) <br>In Kunark the Giant Fort and the mines of nurga. Not many people go to the mines of Nurga but they are right next to the Giant Fort and it has a 12% EXP bonus. VERY good exp. Be careful though because adds come easy here. My suggestion is to become very close friends with a chanter. They have to be the best teammate a shaman can have. MYself and my chater friend along with my pet and his charmed pet can pretty much take out any area we have tried.<br>Also the Dreadlands. This place is pretty overrated in my opinion but it is decent EXP constant pulls and I have found a group within 5 minutes everytime. don't try fighting here until about lvl 38 though.... otherwise youll have a hard time even getting your spells to stick on the mobs.<br>Well thats my 2 Cents. anyone likes what I have to say or has any questions for me please feel free to msg me online..... my Char name is <br>Yakuul Dremora &lt;Mystic Healers&gt; also you can email me at Tyler@qqest.com<br><br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Nov&nbsp;&nbsp;7 11:14:34 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Rive Padishar<br>Druid<br>XEV</td></tr>
